# üêû bug report

### Affected Package

HttpResponse.clone() in packages/common/http/src/response.ts
https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/154129b9defa9295f4684c595d1981c9b3c970c5/packages/common/http/src/response.ts#L289-L303

### Is this a regression?

The implementation of this method was not changed since the release (4.3.0, commit 37797e2b4e1ddc6560ae6c8364ea678ffbaa3de1).

### Description

HttpResponse.clone() does not create a deep copy of fields (body, headers...). Instead, it just uses the standard JavaScript approach to copy the object reference. Therefore, passing cloned HttpReponse can allow receiver to edit the original object

SO thread:
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/66926776/angular-httpresponse-clone-does-not-create-a-new-object


